What will be the Output? Explain why?

		String str1 = "core java";
		String str2 = "core java";
		
		System.out.println(str1.equals(str2));   //True
		System.out.println(str1 == str2);		 //True
		
		String str3 = new String("core java");
		String str4 = new String("core java");
		
		System.out.println(str3.equals(str4));	 //True
		System.out.println(str3 == str4);		 //False
How to make a class singelton?
	Answer:
		public class Singelton{
		public static Singelton instanceOfClass;
		
		private Singelton(){
		}
		public static Singelton getInstance(){
			if(instanceOfClass == null){
				instanceOfClass = new Singelton();
			}
			return instanceOfClass;
			}
		}
